narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Research skills, working with large data sets, putting together presentation and graphs.
I learned how to conduct hands-on lab work and disseminate findings.
You get real hands on lab experience and exposure to how graduate school would be like in engineering, which is amazing if youre thinking about it. I worked in Professor John Fortnera lab.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Weakness: I wish that there was a sort of syllabus or structure laid out in the very beginning to establish what expectations were for the class and the end of the class. Strengths were obviously getting to work closely with a professor and learn from them!
This course is very unstructured, which can be seen as both a strength and a weakness. There are no set syllabus and deliverables, so the class is really what you make of it.
The strengths are that there was a very welcoming reception from the graduate students in the lab, which really helps to have a positive experience.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: You are probably only taking this course if you're in the major, in which case you don't really have a choice.
